definition.value: A glycosyl glycoside consisting of two alpha-D-galactopyranose residues joined by a (1->1) glycosidic bond.

A branched amino hexasaccharide that is beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc in which the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 3 of the mannosyl residue have been glycosylated by beta-D-xylopyranosyl and alpha-D-mannopyranosyl residues respectively, while the GlcNAc residue at the reducing end carries also an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached via a (1->3)-linkage.
An amino disaccharide consisting of a beta-D-galactopyranose residue and a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose and D-galactitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
